article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas -- — Rayshon Harrison had 15 points in Grand Canyon's 53-51 victory over Stephen F. Austin on Thursday night. Harrison was 4 of 9 shooting, including 0 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 7 for 8 from the line for the Antelopes (18-2, 8-1 Western Athletic Conference). Gabe McGlothan scored 11 points while shooting 3 for 8, including 3 for 3 from beyond the arc. Tyon Grant-Foster shot 2 for 10 (0 for 3 from 3-point range) and 5 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with nine points. Latrell Jossell finished with 14 points and five assists for the Lumberjacks (12-7, 5-3). Stephen F. Austin also got 11 points and 11 rebounds from Jalil Beaubrun. Kyle Hayman also put up four points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
